Nakumatt Holdings yesterday said upcountry stores are driving its sales in the back-to-school rush. The largest retail chain by market share said there has been notable rise in customer traffic year-on-year in its Nanyuki, Meru, Kakamega, Bungoma, Busia, Eldoret, Kitale, Nakuru and the entire coast region. &ldquo;We have registered a 12 per cent sales and 27 per cent customer traffic growth in the first two days of the year compared to a similar period last year,&rdquo; managing director Atul Shah said. He noted the retailer&rsquo;s upcountry stores have more customers than those in urban areas. The firm has increased its stock in essential back-to-school products.